==English==
===Etymology===
Named after [[w:Johann Wilhelm Hittorf|Johann Wilhelm Hittorf]] (1824-1914) who first produced it in 1865.  (Reference: John Emsley, ''The Shocking History of Phosphorus'', 2000, ISBN 0-330-39005-8, page 304.)
===Noun===
'''Hittorf's [[phosphorus]]'''
# {{chemistry}} A [[purple]] [[crystal]]ine [[allotrope]] of [[phosphorus]].